Diagnosis. Males of this new species resemble
O. yangi
Zhang, Fu & Zhu, 2009
in lacking a TA (see Fig. 9C and fig. 3 in
Zhang et al. 2009
), but can be distinguished by the wide RTA with a bulge medially ( vs thin and without bulge, compare Fig. 9B with fig. 4 in
Zhang et al . 2009
), and the hook-shaped embolus ( vs slightly curved embolus, compare Fig. 9C with fig. 3 in
Zhang et al . 2009
). Females can be distinguished by the large oval copulatory openings ( vs small and circular, compare Fig. 9E with fig. 7 in
Zhang et al . 2009
) and the large oval spermathecae ( vs small and circular, compare Fig. 9F with fig. 8 in
Zhang et al. 2009
).
